                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " and intentional control of up and down trend of core temperature by "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "1.6^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " are demonstrated for "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": ">60"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " min. Experiments have also shown the induced thermal fluctuations in external calorimetric systems at "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "10^{- 3}^{\\circ}\\mathrm{C}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " level for "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
                                    "content": "60 - 90\\mathrm{min}"
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1262,
                                        1876,
                                        2312,
                                        2669
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": ", which point to biophysical dimension of such phenomena. To explain these results, the biophysical hypothesis consists in the spin conversion of water isomers [18]. The spin configuration affects chemical reactivity [19], [20], behavior in electric field [21], magnetic moment [22], evaporation [23], surface tension [24] and other properties, in particular, the heat capacity of water isomers [25]. As a hypothesis, it is assumed that such a spin conversion induced through ASC, as recently proposed in neuroscience [26], [27] e.g. via non- classical brain functions [28], can cause the observed thermal effects."
                                }
                            ]
                        }
